02/08/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- While acknowledging that several criminal acts have occurred recently, BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak insisted on Friday (30 July) that the security situation in BiH is not alarming.
He added that the upcoming reform of police forces and the strengthening of state-level institutions, especially the State Border Service and the BiH Intelligence Agency, would further improve the security situation.
(FENA - 30/07/04)
